< name>
Juan Carlos Davenport</name>
<Date>1585442525094<//Date>< Rating>
4</Rating>
<review>If I were some this place up in a phrase: it has potential. The equipment itself (the tables) is taken care of well enough, however the actual location as a whole always seems like it would need some general TLC. The menu itself, although it's a pool hall, isn't bad but could use a revamp-prices are fair, and a general remodel/refresh for the entire location wouldn't do it bad either.

For 3 cushion or carom billiards, there is no better place/equipment in the whole of Southern California-this could most likely be attributed to the fact that the previous owner was one of the best 3 cushion players in the world-no joke! Those tables are better maintained than the pool tables, although the pool tables are maintained quite well-definitely far better than your average sports bar.

The crowd of regulars mostly gathers there to play "golfito" on the larger snooker tables, and the atmosphere of the place is well enough that it could be deemed "family-friendly," although there is also room for improvement here.

Bringing your own pool cue would be highly recommended, as the house cues have definitely seen better days, but if you want a fun night out to hang out with your friends, this is definitely a place to go and have a good time.<//review>< pics>

<Rating>5<//Rating>< Review>
After reading other reviews, I wanted to make mine a little more detailed. I came up from Merced to spend a week painting in the mountains. I forgot a few things. One was paint. For such a small town, I was impressed with the amount of space this store had and the selection of various items. The local grocery store [ which i also like] has less of a selection. The paint guy there helped me pick affordable paint, tinted to a color  suited for the purpose it would be used. He made sure I had a can opener and stir stick. I picked up a couple more items and was rung out by a pleasant girl and spoke with a man about a sample I picked up on hard water stain remover. For me...great service, very helpful. There was enough staff to point me around. I would take this experience over most I have in Merced any day.</Review>

<rating>4<//rating><review>It is typically unclear what counts as a "family" restaurant. There are pizza parlors. There are burger joints. The local Mexican food. Prepare to have your mind blown, as this is possibly THE family restaurant.
Perhaps it is the bias that comes from getting grilled cheese here since I was five. Maybe it was the time two years ago, when I worked out a custom dish with the chef. (Presumably Amy?) Maybe it is just that they recognize you after you do not visit for years.
In any case, it is a good, typically quiet, place to have a meal. If you like diner food at its least pretentious, look here... But also their noodles? The food is good. Just... Trust me.< /review>< Pics>

< Text>
Decent fresh food and clean restaurant.  It took  a long time to get our dine in order (over 30 min). There was only one take out oder ahead of us at 2 in the afternoon.

A meal for our family of four  (patty melt, cheese burger, o rings,  egg rolls, chicken chow mein, and sweet and sour chicken with steamed rice) without drinks was over $70 (before tip).

The egg rolls (with Chinese meatloaf inside) were microwaved and then deep fried. They tasted good but we had never had that kind of egg roll filling. Chow mein was made with linquine noodles and was a bit light on flavor. Sandwiches are a la cart (waiter didn't mention). Onion rings were good. Sweet and sour chicken was great... but served over rice so the rice was drowned in sauce (not so kid friendly).  Also they don't have a kids menu.< /Text>

<userid>100296662002973392942</userid><name>Bernardette Congdon</name><Date>1537841417834< /Date><Rating>5< /Rating><review>Our group of 4 were in town for a family wedding. <Rating>5< /Rating>< review>
While the food isn't gourmet, it IS quite good and without a doubt, made with love and patience. We had egg foo young, which was full of whole fresh vegetables and eggs, full of flavor. Pancakes were yummy, and he made them small just for my daughter, even though they normally come larger. Small orange juice was actually very large AND he refilled it for free...and it was organic.
Kung Pao Chicken was relatively salty, but also full of flavor. Best of all is the service...amazingly sweet, full of character, and definitely a home cooked feel. Only thing missing was some background music...
We'll definitely go back.</review>

< Review>
Reviews about this business are quite strange. Check all the reviews, they're pretty much in the same format.

1. Reviews are quite long for a five stars. Usually when bad experiences occur that's when paragraphs upon paragraphs are made. (There are those few times when a person goes into detail about how a business or person went above and beyond and will write a long review to go into detail, but that's quite rare.)

2. Reviews have a tone of "kissing a$$" think of having a family member making a review for your business.

3. Majority of *five star reviewers* accounts only have one review in their total account history.

4. Names are mention in practically all five stars reviews. (Names being mentioned in stellar reviews are not uncommon, but for every five star review that's a pattern)

5. Reviewers names are pretty generic

6.  For being an insurance company and the reviewers having SO much good things to say, it is within human nature to show off what a great deal they got. Although, almost none mention any dollar figures or vehicle type.< /Review>

I spoke with Daniel, he was very friendly and helpful.
I was looking for new car insurance and so I was shopping around seeing which rate would be best suited for my budget. I received a call from Daniel and he quoted me at a very good rate but I still wasn't sure so I told him my situation of how I was still shopping around and he was very understanding, I didn't receive any pressure at all from him, he gave me his contact information and said that he could save the rate that he quoted me at.
I then received a call from another broker from a different company and that person was very pushy and I caved and signed up with them. The next day I regretted my decision and canceled my policy with that broker and called Daniel to see if I could get insurance with him. He told me to make sure that I was actually canceled with the other broker first before starting a new policy with him and so I did. Two weeks later I received confirmation that my policy with the other company had been canceled so I called Daniel back up and just like he said, he was able to get me the rate that he had quoted me at 2 weeks earlier so I of course signed with him.
Im super grateful about the excellent customer service that Daniel provided me with. I definitely would recommend going with this company if youre shopping around for insurance.< /Review>

Maybe I made a mistake by not getting a burger like past reviewers but I wanted to be different so instead I got a Fish Burger. It was basically like 3 fish sticks fried with tartar sauce and shredded lettuce. No flavor at all! For almost $7 for the sandwich alone i would rather have gotten 2 or 3 Filet-O-Fish sandwiches from McDonald's seriously! I will come back because I want to try a burger next time as well as a shake. Place was rather small but clean and the young lady that took my order was very polite! Hopefully a burger can encourage me to give them more stars next time! They accept debit, they have outdoor seating and even a order window outside if dont want to order inside.</Review>
